Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.30,0:00:02.84,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.84,0:00:05.84,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}High school student Shin'ichi was\Nforced to take a drug that shrunk him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.84,0:00:08.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Although smaller, my mind remains\Nthat of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.81,0:00:12.38,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A review of the last episode\Nwill accompany the theme song!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.38,0:00:15.59,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's a big ship,\Nbut there's always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.29,0:01:49.06,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We were nearly stranded on an island
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:52.86,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}before we were picked up by a ship that the Hatamoto family had reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.86,0:01:57.30,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Including the three of us and the butler, there were only ten people onboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:01:59.37,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}On our way back to land, Gozo Hatamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.37,0:02:02.51,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}head of the Hatamoto family, was murdered in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:04.31,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The main suspect was Takeshi Hatamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.31,0:02:06.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who entered the family by marrying Natsue Hatamoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.81,0:02:09.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He turned out to be the son of Isao Zaiki,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.35,0:02:13.98,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who killed himself after Gozo took over his company 10 years earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:18.12,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Since he had a motive, everyone decided to lock Takeshi in a storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.12,0:02:22.43,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It looked like the case was closed, but there was more to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:25.93,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Tatsuo Hatamoto, Akie's husband, was found dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.93,0:02:28.86,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and Takeshi had escaped from the storeroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.36,0:02:46.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:47.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.91,0:02:50.24,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Akie Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.49,0:02:48.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.06,0:02:52.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This never would've happened
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.06,0:02:54.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if you hadn't brought Takeshi into our family!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.77,0:02:56.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have to say for yourself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.09,0:02:59.80,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)\move(162,321,82,321)}Kitaro Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.09,0:02:59.80,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)\move(421,321,341,321)}Ichiro Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.90,0:02:58.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly are lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.34,0:03:04.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s killed Father, all of his fortune belongs to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.06,0:03:04.81,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,0)\move(484,321,404,321)}Mariko Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.18,0:03:09.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious! I don't care about his fortune!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:13.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still not certain that Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the one responsible, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:16.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.99,0:03:21.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The storeroom door was unlocked when we checked it out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.46,0:03:23.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.46,0:03:25.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have gotten out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.73,0:03:27.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,unless someone unlocked it from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.33,0:03:29.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.30,0:03:31.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no signs of damage on the door, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.40,0:03:33.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So if someone did unlock it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.87,0:03:36.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then he has an accomplice in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:49.90,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:53.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So let me get this straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.82,0:03:57.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time of Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.61,0:04:00.07,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Joji Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.16,0:04:00.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the three of you were alone in your private rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.90,0:04:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while you two were together in your shared room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.57,0:04:08.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I couldn't sleep, so I went for a little walk...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:11.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that just like the first murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:14.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,aside from everyone who was with Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.15,0:04:16.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody here has an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:20.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me! My husband just died!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.12,0:04:23.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am {\i1}I{\i0} a suspect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.39,0:04:27.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the one who's happiest to see him dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.93,0:04:33.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that you've been seeing other men!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.66,0:04:37.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You{\i0} had a big enough reason to kill Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.64,0:04:41.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who wanted his inheritance the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.14,0:04:44.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, you two! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.51,0:04:51.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you draw that, Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.08,0:04:53.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.75,0:04:56.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And your son Ichiro isn't exempt either!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.75,0:04:58.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.62,0:05:00.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he was pretty pissed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.39,0:05:03.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after Grandfather tore up his prize-winning drawing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.83,0:05:08.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Father's fault—he never recognized this boy's talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.27,0:05:11.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo always made fun of you, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.17,0:05:13.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Depressed introvert" and stuff like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.50,0:05:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.91,0:05:20.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who wanted to be free of Grandfather the most...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.95,0:05:23.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Uncle Kitaro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.65,0:05:25.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.38,0:05:27.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:28.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:30.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be alright by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.19,0:05:34.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine. I'm not a weakling like my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.96,0:05:36.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:38.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Butler...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.73,0:05:42.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen between Kitaro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:46.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kitaro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} has wanted to leave the Hatamoto family for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.70,0:05:50.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he doesn't have the ambition to run the family company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.47,0:05:54.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the master was greatly opposed to the idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.14,0:05:56.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if {\i1}he{\i0} wasn't against it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.41,0:06:00.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think his wife Mariko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} would have allowed it either...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:05.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.29,0:06:09.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 20 minutes, but Ichiro still isn't back from the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.29,0:06:11.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me Takeshi got him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.93,0:06:18.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down! Stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.07,0:06:21.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! But Ichiro isn't back yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.51,0:06:22.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:25.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't leave the room, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.31,0:06:27.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Ran and Conan! Are you there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.38,0:06:28.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.61,0:06:30.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.05,0:06:31.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the electrical room!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.88,0:06:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You two head for the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.45,0:06:37.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The restrooms were this way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:41.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't that Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:43.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.60,0:06:46.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.17,0:06:50.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:52.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-My leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.80,0:06:54.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.71,0:06:56.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's alright! The wound isn't deep!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.37,0:06:58.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to bandage it up right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.01,0:07:00.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the first-aid kit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:02.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who did this to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.91,0:07:04.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.11,0:07:08.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The lights suddenly went out and then I sensed someone come in...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.72,0:07:10.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then they stabbed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.69,0:07:15.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.89,0:07:18.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...{\i1}my{\i0} knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.80,0:07:20.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me {\i1}you{\i0} did this, Joji!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.80,0:07:22.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.93,0:07:25.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was with you all in the dining room\Nwhen the power went out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.74,0:07:27.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't have done this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.34,0:07:28.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.94,0:07:32.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one person who could have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.51,0:07:34.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.41,0:07:37.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not necessarily the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.41,0:07:40.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Ran take care of Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s bandage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.72,0:07:44.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like the rest of you to come to the electrical room with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.46,0:07:48.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.66,0:07:51.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Have a look for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.93,0:07:54.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:56.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a type of timing device.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.27,0:07:59.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This one is simple enough for anyone to set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.18,0:08:02.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You attach a heavy weight to the breaker,\Nbalance it around a fulcrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.68,0:08:05.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then put a candle in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.65,0:08:09.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After enough time passes, the rope burns apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.75,0:08:12.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which causes the weight to pull down on the breaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.46,0:08:14.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from how much of the candle has melted,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.76,0:08:17.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this was all set up quite a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.09,0:08:22.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, any one of you could be\Nresponsible for the power outage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.47,0:08:26.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I'll take the responsibility of finding Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.47,0:08:31.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I do, I don't want any of you\Nto take a step out of the dining room!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.84,0:08:48.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt, Ichiro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.04,0:08:49.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:51.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we've looked this hard but still haven't found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.61,0:08:54.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe he's not on the ship anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:57.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we've searched everywhere yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.72,0:09:00.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like everyone's rooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.26,0:09:09.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not in Kitaro's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:15.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These two seem to have rather different personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.50,0:09:17.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is their marriage holding up well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.47,0:09:21.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They're both cousins, and although it may not look like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.34,0:09:24.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they've been good friends since they were little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.61,0:09:27.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-They're cousins and they're married?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.28,0:09:29.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.52,0:09:32.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the master was extremely opposed to them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.99,0:09:34.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Them, too"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:44.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't look like he's in Joji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:47.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is this his knife case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:48.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.60,0:09:54.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two of his knives are missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.64,0:09:55.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.78,0:09:59.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One knife we found right after Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was attacked,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:01.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but where's the other one?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.25,0:10:06.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:08.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? These are his drawings!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.49,0:10:11.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's no reason to enter the room carelessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.03,0:10:14.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} could be hiding in here with a weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.60,0:10:17.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, he's really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.03,0:10:20.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, maybe there's a drawing of the murder scene here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:23.70,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:30.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, don't touch those!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:31.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.82,0:10:36.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not in here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.83,0:10:38.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.82,0:10:40.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.62,0:10:43.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Charcoal. You use it for rough sketches.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.42,0:10:44.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.22,0:10:48.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, get the lead out. We're moving on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:49.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.01,0:10:52.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ordinary eraser.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:55.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.45,0:11:00.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't in our rooms or in Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.78,0:11:04.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is Akie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.12,0:11:09.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he's not on the ship anymore—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.26,0:11:12.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.66,0:11:15.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:16.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:19.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's return to the dining room for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.84,0:11:26.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey! Mr. Butler!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.18,0:11:27.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know if...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.55,0:11:32.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did that ever happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.15,0:11:37.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find out?\NOnly the master and I know about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.29,0:11:39.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So I'm right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.76,0:11:42.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The first incident, in which Mr. Gozo was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.49,0:11:47.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The bread found near the body,\Nand the location of the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:49.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The second incident, in which Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r} was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:53.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The splash and thud sounds\NI heard at the time of the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:56.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The person who unlocked the storeroom door...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.77,0:12:01.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And then the third incident, in which Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r} was stabbed in the dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.75,0:12:04.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Each of these mysteries is connected by a single thread!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.26,0:12:14.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come here a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.66,0:12:18.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.06,0:12:20.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.07,0:12:28.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.91,0:12:32.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.71,0:12:34.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He has something important to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.41,0:12:38.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he wants everyone to come to Akie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room in 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.55,0:12:41.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something important to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.15,0:12:42.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:49.13,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come on! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.13,0:12:52.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old man's voice is #59...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.00,0:12:55.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.03,0:13:00.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Someone on this ship was responsible for all three incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.47,0:13:02.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.87,0:13:04.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's obviously him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.78,0:13:06.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Takeshi's doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.34,0:13:08.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, just calm down...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:12.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I reveal the killer's name, let us look at the incidents again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.88,0:13:15.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First was Incident #1, in which\NMr. Gozo was murdered in his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:19.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which had been locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.12,0:13:21.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From the fact that there was blood on the doorframe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.66,0:13:25.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Gozo likely escaped back into his room after he was stabbed outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.26,0:13:30.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He then locked the door, but fell lifeless soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.40,0:13:33.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We later found a flower on the ground, in front of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.84,0:13:37.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Takeshi was wearing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.38,0:13:39.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means he did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:41.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is one strange detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.98,0:13:45.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though Mr. Gozo was stabbed outside his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.22,0:13:47.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there were no blood marks in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.75,0:13:49.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure the killer didn't wipe it up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.75,0:13:52.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to delay us from discovering the corpse?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.79,0:13:54.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not refuting that fact;
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.19,0:13:58.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying that the flower fell\N{\i1}after{\i0} the blood was wiped up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.53,0:14:00.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand if the killer accidentally dropped it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.70,0:14:02.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while stabbing the victim and then escaping...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.90,0:14:05.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the killer meticulously wiped up the blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.64,0:14:09.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By leaving the flower there, everyone would've noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:12.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially if it was dropped during the middle of cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.54,0:14:16.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the killer purposely left the flower on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.25,0:14:19.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to make Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} look guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.32,0:14:23.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is Incident #2, in which Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.59,0:14:26.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the first incident with its flower
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.16,0:14:29.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the third incident with its fancy set-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.19,0:14:32.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this incident lacked any sort of artificiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.46,0:14:35.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If these were all indeed done by the same person,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.13,0:14:42.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,my guess is that the second murder was an unplanned one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.31,0:14:45.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, {\i1}why{\i0} was Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:49.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to that question is in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.48,0:14:52.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my knife case!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:55.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a look. Two knives are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.35,0:14:58.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found one of them at the scene of Incident #3,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.53,0:15:00.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but where did the other one go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.39,0:15:05.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The main point here is in the two sounds that Conan heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.00,0:15:08.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The thud was likely the sound of the killer striking Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.87,0:15:12.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but what was the splash that came before it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.20,0:15:13.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what I'm thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:18.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The splash sound was the other knife from this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.98,0:15:21.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just happened to see it thrown overboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:24.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer could have killed him to keep things quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.98,0:15:27.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would make the most sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.19,0:15:31.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Takeshi vanished from the storeroom after the second incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.99,0:15:34.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Takeshi is the most suspicious here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.86,0:15:39.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that storeroom door was locked from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.26,0:15:41.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Escape would have been impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.43,0:15:42.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,unless someone unlocked it for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.70,0:15:44.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.44,0:15:46.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who opened it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.14,0:15:49.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.07,0:15:51.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder wasn't part of the killer's plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.61,0:15:55.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and it took place while Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.18,0:15:58.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer worked so hard to make Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} look guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.05,0:16:01.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but this second murder would do just the opposite and prove his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.95,0:16:05.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer unlocked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.86,0:16:08.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was done to make it look like Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.29,0:16:11.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,had the ability to murder Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.20,0:16:14.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then why did Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.30,0:16:16.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We {\i1}still{\i0} haven't found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.83,0:16:19.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have him explain that himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.77,0:16:24.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Why don't you stop hiding and come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.64,0:16:27.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in this room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:30.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.72,0:16:39.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:44.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, tell us what happened when you escaped from the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.16,0:16:47.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I thought something happened to Natsue...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.80,0:16:49.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't stand around doing nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.60,0:16:52.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and as I was pounding on the door,\Nit suddenly unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.80,0:16:54.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.67,0:16:57.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then when I went up to the deck...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.01,0:16:59.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi did it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.71,0:17:01.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.75,0:17:04.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Realizing that I would be blamed again,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.32,0:17:07.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran into Akie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room,\Nwhose door just happened to be open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.62,0:17:10.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I stayed inside the closet the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.62,0:17:13.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the person who stabbed Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} during Incident #3
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.69,0:17:15.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't him either...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.63,0:17:17.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.23,0:17:19.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they do something this horrible to Ichiro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.73,0:17:23.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the killer made a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.90,0:17:24.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:28.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Unlocking the storeroom door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.97,0:17:31.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer had managed to frame Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.98,0:17:36.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but now it looked like he had an accomplice who had let him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.25,0:17:40.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't until then that anyone started to suspect the real killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.38,0:17:43.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Flustered, the murderer came up with a scheme
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.69,0:17:45.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid any further suspicion:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.86,0:17:50.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Incident #3, in which Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked in the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.86,0:17:57.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was in this incident that the killer dug his own grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.30,0:18:01.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the darkness, the killer shouldn't have been able to see Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.97,0:18:06.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, he was clearly able to see Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} well enough to stab him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.31,0:18:08.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.31,0:18:11.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, the weapon was found lying at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:17.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the first two incidents,\Nthe attacker didn't leave with the weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:20.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the attacker {\i1}couldn't{\i0} have left with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.73,0:18:25.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he couldn't go anywhere with his injured leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.00,0:18:28.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean to say—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.83,0:18:29.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.97,0:18:33.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who stabbed him...was Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.30,0:18:37.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who killed Mr. Gozo and Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.94,0:18:42.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.85,0:18:46.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.18,0:18:48.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you put the lights out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.32,0:18:52.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was because you didn't want to identify your attacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.16,0:18:57.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you said it was Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and then he was found innocent later,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.53,0:19:00.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then all the suspicion would fall onto you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.67,0:19:03.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all conjecture!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.27,0:19:06.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any evidence that Ichiro's the murderer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.27,0:19:08.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.21,0:19:13.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The piece of bread that was found near Mr. Gozo's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.81,0:19:16.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of bread?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.18,0:19:18.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is an art student.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.18,0:19:21.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And right before Mr. Gozo was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:23.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he was drawing a picture on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:26.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bread pieces are sometimes used as erasers for charcoal sketches,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.96,0:19:30.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I hear that these pieces often fall into artists' cuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.16,0:19:35.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When he stabbed Mr. Gozo, that piece of bread fell out of his cuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.23,0:19:38.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It fell {\i1}onto{\i0} Mr. Gozo's blood, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.44,0:19:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, this bread piece has a tiny bit of charcoal on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:46.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no doubt that it was Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} who dropped it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.38,0:19:48.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he has no motive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.48,0:19:50.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro had no reason to kill Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.95,0:19:55.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I, myself, couldn't tell what his motive was until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.35,0:19:58.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I saw something in his room, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.92,0:20:00.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Something in his room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.93,0:20:02.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.33,0:20:06.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s motive for killing Mr. Gozo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.13,0:20:09.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How is a picture his motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.93,0:20:12.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is in the drawing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.80,0:20:15.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see how...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.51,0:20:17.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.68,0:20:19.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.51,0:20:23.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! All these drawings are of Natsue!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.23,0:20:26.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.97,0:20:32.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro! Don't tell me you—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.32,0:20:33.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.56,0:20:38.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was in love with Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.56,0:20:42.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.37,0:20:45.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Suzuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.14,0:20:48.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to reveal your feelings to Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.44,0:20:49.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you went to Mr. Gozo and—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:55.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! I asked him to let me marry Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.38,0:20:58.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he wouldn't hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.52,0:21:01.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He refused to give his beloved Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to someone like me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.59,0:21:04.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And soon after that, almost as if to spite me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.39,0:21:08.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he announced that Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was going to marry Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.66,0:21:12.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then when he yelled at me yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.30,0:21:15.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while I was on the deck, drawing Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.20,0:21:18.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him to give up his hopeless dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.94,0:21:21.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forgive them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.04,0:21:25.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not my grandfather, who refused to let me marry Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.04,0:21:31.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who stole my Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.62,0:23:12.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.69,0:23:18.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still feel the same way toward my grandfather and us?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.09,0:23:20.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}am{\i0} the son of Isao Zaiki,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.39,0:23:25.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who committed suicide after the Hatamoto Group took over his company.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.40,0:23:29.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's true that I got close to you because I hated your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.54,0:23:32.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But ever since I met you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.68,0:23:39.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The tragedy was caused by a shy young man
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.35,0:23:43.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who was unable to put his secret thoughts into words...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.45,0:23:47.62,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The ship is nearing Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.62,0:23:51.80,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}while being bathed by the red sunset that is the sadness and despair
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.80,0:23:53.62,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}of Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r} and the entire Hatamoto family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.99,0:24:11.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She has...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.10,0:24:12.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...amnesia?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.00,0:24:15.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.17,0:24:24.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why is the man from the racetrack after Maya{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.46,0:24:30.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.46,0:24:30.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Case of the Mysterious Woman with Amnesia
